    "This improvement is evident in both MOSEI and MOSI datasets, particularly notable in the MOSEI dataset.",
    "Specifically, the incorporation of the TK and LG modules resulted in enhancements in Acc-2, F1, and Mult acc 5/7 metrics, affirming their positive role in the model, effectively boosting overall performance.For instance, in the MOSI dataset (as seen in Table 5), the model showed improvements in Acc-2, F 1, MAE, and Corr metrics after the integration of TK and LG modules.",
    "Similarly, in the MOSEI dataset (refer to Table 6), the same configuration also demonstrated improvements in these key metrics, especially in Acc-2 and F1 scores, which increased by nearly 2 percentage points.",
    "Notably, despite the enhanced performance, the number of model parameters decreased, indicating that the inclusion of TK and LG modules not only improved the model's performance but also its parameter efficiency.In summary, the experiments conclusively show that the incorporation of the TK and LG modules significantly enhances the overall performance of the model in sentiment analysis on the MOSI and MOSEI datasets, while also improving parameter efficiency.",
    "Therefore, the TK and LG modules represent a beneficial improvement to the sentiment analysis model, enhancing its performance while maintaining efficient parameter configuration.Multi-Modal Emotion Recognition Using Tensor Decomposition Fusion and Self-Supe Case AnalysisIn the course of our experiments, we observed that the textual modality contributed most significantly among the three modalities."
